metadata.name: Keeping the Tempo
metadata.description:
A beautiful architectural image of The Tempodrom in Berlin, Germany. The multi-purpose venue designed to look like a circus tent really is an eye catching structure.  
Photographer Tony Sellen has used the contrast of the building and its striking sharp lines to create this intimidating yet visually pleasing 1:1 piece of artwork.

The collector has the option to receive a physical gallery print.

Keeping the Tempo  
Berlin 2017  
Exposure: 1/320 second at f/7.1  
ISO: 100  
Focal Length:18mm  
Camera: Nikon  
Lens: Nikon
